According to the Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) Rihanna has actually clocked up an astounding 110.5 million song certifications in the US, a first in the digital music age.To achieve just one digital certification under the RIAA's criteria, a track has to be downloaded once - e.g., via a purchase form iTunes or Amazon, etc - or streamed 150 times.On Wednesday morning, Rihanna's record label Universal Music, tweeted the good news.